message:
Declare the Maoni activity in the library manifest

- It is now possible for callers to specify handlers (via the MaoniBuilder, which leverages a Configuration singleton instance)
- Add a beautiful parallax image header
- Pave the way to open-sourcing the whole project outside
Add Travis Build Status Image to README file

Update README

Add simple example to get started with the defaults, and move "Screenshots" section higher in the text
Add support for translations and sync via Travis CI

Update README

Update instructions for build.gradle
Fix Play Store URL for sample app
Update max age for retrieving badges in README

Let callbacks decide whether or not to finish the Maoni activity upon a click on the 'Send Feedback' button

This contains a breaking change in the callbacks API.

Version bump: 2.0

This contains breaking changes in the API:
- The Feedback.Device class has been removed, in favor of a separate DeviceInfo class, which contains everything related to the Device
Temporarily revert to 1.3.0 in README, waiting for artifacts to be effectively available on Bintray / JCenter

Update README to version 2.0

Artifacts are now available in JCenter

Drop 'maxAge' param from Github badges HTTP requests

This allows to retrieve them at every page refresh

Prepare for version bump

- Maoni 2.0.1
- Sample app 2.1.1
Highlight the fact that app logs are also captured
